</i></p><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">The National Health Service (NHS) is a cornerstone of healthcare in the United Kingdom, providing comprehensive and accessible services to millions. At the heart of this vast system is NHS England, a pivotal organisation that oversees the delivery and improvement of healthcare services nationwide. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune will explore the role of NHS England, its significance, and how healthcare providers can ensure compliance with relevant legislation and regulations. </span>
