</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-23_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-24_ pf-text-1"><strong>Budget </strong>- £130 billion+</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-26_ pf-text-1"><strong>Clinical Commissioning Groups (CCGs)</strong> - 200+&nbsp;</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-28_ pf-text-1"><strong>Patients</strong> - Over 1 million patients interact with NHS services every 36 hours</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-30_ pf-text-1"><strong>Workforce </strong>- NHS England employs over 1.2 million people.




 














</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-32_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-33_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-34_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-36_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>NHS England</strong> - Is an executive non-departmental public body of the Department of Health and Social Care. It was established by the Health and Social Care Act 2012 to improve health outcomes for people in England by providing national leadership for the NHS.

</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Clinical Commissioning Groups (CCGs) </strong>- CCGs are clinically led statutory NHS bodies responsible for planning and commissioning healthcare services for their local area. They play a critical role in shaping healthcare delivery to meet local needs.</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-41_ pf-text-1"><strong>Care Quality Commission (CQC) </strong>- The CQC is an independent regulator of health and social care in England. It ensures that healthcare services meet essential standards of quality and safety.





</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-egiyK kKHsVi pf-43_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-ilfuhL ejXpQB pf-44_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-45_ pf-heading-1-h3">The Role of NHS England
</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-47_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong> Setting priorities and goals</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-49_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">NHS England is tasked with setting the strategic direction for healthcare in England. This includes defining priorities such as improving patient outcomes, enhancing the quality of care, and promoting innovation in healthcare delivery.





















</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-51_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong> Resource allocation
</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-53_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">NHS England has a significant responsibility for resource allocation. It distributes funds to CCGs and other healthcare providers, ensuring financial resources are used effectively to meet healthcare demands.






















</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-55_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong> Monitoring and regulation
</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-57_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">NHS England monitors the performance of CCGs and other healthcare providers. It ensures compliance with national standards and regulations, working closely with the CQC to uphold the quality and safety of healthcare services.























</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-59_ pf-heading-1-h3"><strong>Public health initiatives</strong></h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-61_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">NHS England plays a crucial role in public health initiatives, such as vaccination programmes, health screenings, and campaigns to promote healthy lifestyles. These initiatives are crucial for preventing illness and reducing the burden on healthcare services.






















